Monitoring microservices
1) Sleuth and Zipkin.
   Distributed Tracing - To track request by adding trace id. To find the reason of failure and place where it failed
2) Actuator 
   It help us to monitor and manage the Spring Boot application. 
   It contains the actuator endpoints (the place where the resources live).
3) Resilence4j 
   Fault Tolerance (Bulkhead, Time Limiter , Rate Limiter, Circuit Breaker, Retry).
4) AWS CloudWatch & CloudTrail
   AWS CloudWatch monitors your AWS resources and applications, whereas CloudTrail monitors the activity in your AWS environment. 
   For instance, with CloudWatch, you can scale your applications, whereas, with CloudTrail, you can see who did what to your applications

